Sec. 17-33. Housing cost impact analysis.
Prior to the adoption of any ordinance, policy, regulation, or plan provision that will or is likely to affect the cost of housing, the County Manager shall prepare an impact analysis in the form of a written report setting forth the following information concerning the proposed ordinance, policy, regulation, or plan provision;
The purpose of the proposed action and the anticipated direct and indirect benefits and costs to the parties impacted;
The best estimate of the direct or indirect increased cost, if any, on the per unit cost of housing types affected;
The effect of the proposed action on public or private employment;
Whether the proposed action is necessary to enable the County to obtain state or federal grants or other financing, or is legally mandated;
Whether another action could serve the same purpose at less cost to housing; and
If the proposed action is deemed necessary, what actions could be taken to mitigate the cost increase to the home buyer.
